{
  "stem": "5103.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Am I going to see my mommy and daddy?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Am I going to see?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they always said maybe one day, always maybe one day.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then this Mr.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Hertz ?] came one morning and said, we're going to take you now somewhere and you'll be surprised.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But you see, what happened was nobody ever told you anything.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Because if they ever caught a child, they would torture that child till they would tell something.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And something might be just the thing that they-- the hiding places or some connection or a name or something.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So they never, ever said anything until you got to the place.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Wherever you went it was always like a secret mission, which it had to be.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And so this day, back into my little woolen outfit, I went with him, and I went to a place where-- when the door opened-- I saw my mother.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "My mother and my father.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And it was like I had been given a new lease of life.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "My mother held me, I think, the whole day.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And my father sat with his arms around the three of us-- I-- for as long as I can remember.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "It seemed to go on forever, but we had to go to bed at night.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And there was, in that house-- this was in the [? room ?] [INAUDIBLE] in Haarlem-- there was an-- a husband and wife who owned the place, who had a daughter called Rita.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "The daughter Rita was nearly engaged to my Uncle Lou, whom they were hiding, and my grandfather on my father's side, whom they were hiding.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "My mother was there and my father was there, and now that meant-- And there were only like three rooms upstairs.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
